<%# 2026-05-18 — `BundlesController#destroy` Turbo Stream response.

    Three streams composed:

      1. Remove the bundle's shelf tile (`#bundle-tile-<id>`) so it
         disappears from the `/games` bundles outer-shelf row without
         a page reload. The tile component stamps this id on its
         wrapping `<a>` for exactly this purpose.

      2. Replace the bundles modal partial with the steady-state
         render (NO `bundle:` local). This closes the open per-
         bundle modal view (the dialog itself is re-rendered as
         inert; the `bundles-modal-reset` controller fires on the
         native `close` event during the swap and tears down any
         residual per-bundle state). The next tile click starts
         from a clean modal.

      3. Append the flash notice to the toast container. The toast
         container always renders unconditionally in the layout
         (`shared/_flash_toasts`), so an `append` is safe even when
         no flash has fired this page-life. The `toast` Stimulus
         controller self-dismisses after the default delay; the
         `flash-popover` controller promotes the container above
         any still-open dialog via the Popover API top layer.
%>
<%= turbo_stream.remove "bundle-tile-#{@bundle.id}" %>

<%= turbo_stream.replace "bundles-modal" do %>
  <%= render "games/bundles_modal" %>
<% end %>

<%# Remove the per-bundle confirm-delete dialog from the DOM too. The
    dialog is rendered as a sibling of each bundle tile in
    `_bundles_for_shelf`; leaving an orphan `<dialog>` behind after
    its bundle is gone is harmless but tidy to clean up. %>
<%= turbo_stream.remove "confirm_delete_bundle_#{@bundle.id}" %>

<turbo-stream action="append" targets=".toast-container">
  <template>
    <div class="toast toast-notice" data-controller="toast" role="status">
      bundle deleted.
    </div>
  </template>
</turbo-stream>
